s-hero-simple__image-container\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/header>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-bstn-blocks-indented-content-container bstn-blocks-indented-content-container\"><div class=\"row\"><div class=\"bstn-blocks-indented-content-container__content col col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-1\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-bstn-blocks-course-cta-card bstn-blocks-course-cta-card\"><svg xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewbox=\"0 0 14 17\" fill=\"none\" class=\"bstn-blocks-course-cta-card__icon\"><path stroke=\"currentColor\" strokelinecap=\"round\" strokelinejoin=\"round\" d=\"M12.554 16H2.444c-.383 0-.75-.158-1.021-.44A1.53 1.53 0 011 14.5M6.777 2H2.926c-.511 0-1 .21-1.362.586A2.039 2.039 0 001 4v10.5c0-.398.152-.78.423-1.06.27-.282.638-.44 1.021-.44h9.629c.127 0 .25-.053.34-.146a.512.512 0 00.141-.354v-10c0-.133-.05-.26-.14-.354A.481.481 0 0012.072 2h-1.445m.964 14v-3\"><\/path><path stroke=\"currentColor\" strokelinecap=\"round\" strokelinejoin=\"round\" d=\"M10.628 9L8.703 7 6.777 9V2c0-.265.101-.52.282-.707A.941.941 0 017.739 1h1.926c.256 0 .5.105.681.293.18.187.282.442.282.707v7z\"><\/path><\/svg><div class=\"bstn-blocks-course-cta-card__content\"><div role=\"heading\" aria-level=\"2\">Ready to start your career in Marketing? Find our more about BrainStation&#8217;s\u00a0<a class=\"bstn-blocks-course-cta-card__link\" href=\"https:\/\/brainstation.io\/course\/online\/remote-digital-marketing-bootcamp\">Digital Marketing Bootcamp<svg xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" fill=\"none\" class=\"bstn-blocks-course-cta-card__link-icon\"><path fill=\"currentColor\" d=\"M6.345 12.743a1 1 0 001.31 1.511l5.477-4.749a1 1 0 000-1.511l-5.477-4.75a1.001 1.001 0 00-1.31 1.512l4.606 3.993-4.606 3.994z\"><\/path><\/svg><\/a><\/div><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>According to Glassdoor, the average salary for a Social Media Specialist is just over $48,000 and can rise up to $66,000. Once you\u2019ve transitioned into a more experienced managerial position, a Social Media Manager can make between $63,000 and $97,000. The average salary differs depending on your state, company, and experience. In some states, an entry-level social media position will earn you $42,000 with more experienced roles earning approximately $107,000.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some Marketers decide to do freelance or contract jobs for clients on the side. These rates will vary depending on the scope of the project, your experience, and general salary expectations. If you\u2019re a new freelancer, hourly rates usually range between $15 &#8211; $50 per hour, again depending on how advanced the project is and how much experience you have under your belt. For more advanced freelance work, you can charge upwards from $120 per hour.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you\u2019re taking on long-term projects in social media management, monthly fees can range between $400 to $5,000 or even higher depending on how established your agency is, how big the client is, and how big of a campaign they\u2019re looking to accomplish.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-bstn-blocks-heading bstn-blocks-heading bstn-blocks-heading--h2 has-text-align-left\" id=\"how-much-can-social-media-professionals-make?\"><h2 class=\"bstn-blocks-heading__heading-element\">How Much Can Social Media Professionals Make?<\/h2><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-bstn-blocks-indented-content-container bstn-blocks-indented-content-container\"><div class=\"row\"><div class=\"bstn-blocks-indented-content-container__content col col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-1\">\n<p>Social media professionals can make on average $46,678 per year, although that can vary widely, with ZipRecruiter reporting annual salaries as high as $85,500. The majority of salaries within the social media professional jobs category currently range between $31,500 (25th percentile) to $52,500 (75th percentile) across the U.S. Reported salaries are highest at IBM, where the average pay is $67,160. Other companies that offer high salaries for this role include T-Mobile, Inc., paying around $54,000.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-bstn-blocks-content-navigation-footer bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer\"><div class=\"bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__links-container\"><div class=\"bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link-container\"><p class=\"bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link-title bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link--desktop\">Previous Article<\/p><a class=\"bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link\" href=\"https:\/\/brainstation.io\/career-guides\/is-social-media-specialist-a-good-career\"><span class=\"bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link-icon-wrapper bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link-icon-wrapper--left\"><svg xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" fill=\"none\" class=\"bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link-icon bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link-icon--left\"><path fill=\"currentColor\" d=\"M6.345 12.743a1 1 0 001.31 1.511l5.477-4.749a1 1 0 000-1.511l-5.477-4.75a1.001 1.001 0 00-1.31 1.512l4.606 3.993-4.606 3.994z\"><\/path><\/svg><\/span><span class=\"bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link-text bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link--desktop\">Is Social Media Specialist a Good Career?<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class=\"bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link-container\"><p class=\"bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link-title\">Next Article<\/p><a class=\"bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link\" href=\"https:\/\/brainstation.io\/career-guides\/social-media-cover-letters\"><span class=\"bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link-text\">Social Media Cover Letters<\/span><span class=\"bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link-icon-wrapper bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link-icon-wrapper--right\"><svg xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" fill=\"none\" class=\"bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link-icon bstn-blocks-content-nav-footer__link-icon--right\"><path fill=\"currentColor\" d=\"M6.345 12.743a1 1 0 001.31 1.511l5.477-4.749a1 1 0 000-1